author: jonl
msg: Final checkin for RC1.  Changed initModel in Component to search the whole parent
hierarchy for CompoundModels.  Added logic that allows Components to know if they
are the root model or a child sharing the parent's compound model.  This allowed
me to remove getRootModelObject() and incorporate the logic necessary to get the
right model directly into getModelObject(), which now always works.  It also made
it possible to make replication of objects using compound models vastly more
efficient since Components that inherit models are now detected and nulled out in
detachModel().  When the Component is deserialized, the model will be null and it
will be initialied via initModel() when needed as it originally was.  Made changes
to Images and ImageButtons so that they search for models differently (as a last
resort, actually).  This means they can be used with CompoundModels like any other
Component, although that use-case should be rare.
